WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.000
In October 2023, the Biden Administration issued an Executive Order on the Safe, Secure, and Trustworthy Development and Use of Artificial Intelligence.

2
00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:16.500
This Executive Order is a tremendous step in providing the accountability and protections we need,

3
00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:21.500
while pushing toward innovation that could dramatically improve the quality of services that the government can deliver.

4
00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:24.500
Using the framework set by the Executive Order

5
00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:29.500
the Office of Management and Budget developed draft policy guidance to drive innovative uses of AI at Federal agencies,

6
00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.250
while ensuring this work is done responsibly.

7
00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:38.000
OMB’s draft guidance outlines three pillars to advance the responsible use of AI in government:

8
00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:47.000
Strengthening AI governance, through the designation of Chief AI Officers that hold primary responsibility for managing risks from their agency’s use of AI;

9
00:00:47.500 --> 00:00:55.000
Advancing responsible AI innovation, through the removal of barriers to the responsible use of AI and the development of agency AI strategies

10
00:00:55.500 --> 00:01:03.500
; and Managing risks from the use of AI, through the adoption of minimum AI risk management practices for uses of AI that impact rights and safety.

11
00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:13.000
With this draft guidance, the government is demonstrating that it can lead in AI and ensure that the technology benefits all.


